Extensive deforestation of cedar trees in South and Central America has led the European Union to consider trade restrictions.
Germany, holding the EU presidency, highlights the vulnerability of the spiny dogfish due to overfishing.
Other species like Brazilian lobsters and sawfish are also at risk.
The UN Environment Programme warns of threats to biodiversity from habitat destruction and climate change.
Conservation efforts are crucial, as seen in the protection of Caribbean coral species.
The global trade of red coral faces regulation to ensure sustainability.
Tourism plays a key role in supporting coral reef conservation efforts worldwide.
